{{Wiktionary|cricket}}
'''[[Cricket]]''' is a bat-and-ball sport contested by two teams.

'''Cricket''' may also refer to:
{{TOC right}}
<!--keep to top-->
* [[Cricket (insect)]], family Gryllidae, also known as "true crickets"
** [[Tettigoniidae]], known as katydids or bush-crickets

== Entertainment ==
* [[Cricket (musical)|''Cricket'' (musical)]], a musical by Andrew Lloyd Webber and Tim Rice
* ''Cricket'', nickname of the character [[Christine Blair]] in ''The Young and the Restless''
* ''Cricket'', character played by Hoagy Carmichael in the film ''[[To Have and Have Not (film)|To Have and Have Not]]''
* ''Cricket'', character in the 1988 novel ''[[Fire on the Mountain (1988 novel)|Fire on the Mountain]]''
* [[The Crickets]], a rock and roll band formed by Buddy Holly
* "Cricket", a song by The Kinks on their album ''[[Preservation Act 1]]''
* [[Crickets (album)|''Crickets'' (album)]], an album by Joe Nichols
* "Crickets", a song by [[Drop City Yacht Club]]
* [[Shturcite]], a Bulgarian rock and roll band formed in 1967 translated as The Crickets in English
* [[The Crickets (album)|''The Crickets'' (album)]], compilation album by Shturcite

== Publications and literature ==
* [[Cricket (magazine)|''Cricket'' (magazine)]], an American literary magazine for children
* ''Cricket'', a translation into English of the Polish poem ''[[ChrzÄ…szcz]]'' by Jan Brzechwa
* [[The Cricket (magazine)|''The Cricket'' (magazine)]], a 19th-century American general-interest magazine, named after the insect

== Vehicles ==
* [[Cricket (1914 automobile)]], an early American automobile
* [[Plymouth Cricket (disambiguation)]], two automobiles
* [[Cricket (airplane)]], a light plane

== Telecommunications ==
* [[Cricket Communications]] also known as Cricket Wireless, a wireless service provider subsidiary of Leap Wireless

== Other uses ==
* [[Cricket (darts)]], a game using the standard 20-number dartboard
* [[Programmable Cricket]], robotic toys
* [[Cricket (roofing)]], a ridge structure designed to divert water on a roof
* [[Cricket, North Carolina]]
* ''Cricket'', a type of spinning [[float (breakdancing move)]]
* [[Cricket (warning sound)]], an audible warning in the cockpits of commercial aircraft

